        <tr>
            <td width="137" rowspan="3"><img src="articleImage.php?ArticleID=482&amp;ImageNumber=2" width="531" /></td>
            <td width="15" rowspan="3">&nbsp;</td>
            <td width="182">    <img src="authorImage.php?ID=22" style="max-width: 50px; max-height: 50px; float: left; margin: 5px;" /> By <a href="" target="_blank">Liz Boyer</a><br/><br/>
    
    The recently released, 'Masters of Fashion Illustration' is a collection of some of the finest art ever created in the name of fashion. This beautiful book describes and showcases the often colorful lives and stunning work of the greatest 20th century fashion illustrators as chosen by the discerning eye of one of world's finest contemporary fashion artists, David Downton.<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;
In the introduction, Downton recollects the moment he first experienced fashion nirvana at his first couture show (one of Gianni Versace's last) in Paris in 1996. Those were the days when Naomi, Kate and Linda owned the runways and provided illustrators like the author with countless opportunities to let the outside world a brief and intimate glimpse into the world of couture.&#8203;<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;
Downton makes no claims of impartiality in  his comprehensive selection of "super draughtsmen (who) ... told not just the story of the dress, describing the time, the place and the woman...				<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" id="articleFunctions">
					<tr>
											<td><a href="#more" onclick="showMore();"><img src="images/read_more.jpg" alt="read more" /></a></td>
											<td><a href="#commentsDisplay"><img src="images/comments.jpg" alt="comments" /></a></td>
											<td><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Obrj3gG-rO0"><img src="images/play_video.jpg" alt="play video" /></a></td>
										</tr>
					<tr>
											<td style=""><a href="#more" onclick="showMore();">read more</a></td>
											<td style=""><a href="#commentsDisplay">comments</a></td>
											<td style=""><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Obrj3gG-rO0">video</a></td>
